      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Focus the description entirely on the protagonist’s internal state of alienation rather than describing the crowd as inherently dangerous. Convey the feeling of being an outsider by detailing how their own presence feels conspicuous; maybe their lighter clothing or unfamiliar gait draws an uncomfortable focus from the onlookers. Describe the periphery—the way eyes sweep over the protagonist with an unsettling economy of movement, or the silence that suddenly drops when they pass a doorway. This external pressure reflects their own mounting, personalized anxiety about violating unspoken local codes.",
